meta {
  name: POST climatisation (legacy bare endpoint, multi-purpose)
  type: http
  seq: 25
}

post {
  url: {{base_url}}/v2/vehicles/{{vin}}/climatisation
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
  Accept: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "action": "settings",
    "targetTemperature_K": 295.15
  }
}

docs {
  Multi-purpose climatisation-action endpoint. Body shapes:
    {"action": "settings", "targetTemperature_K": <K>}    ← shown
    {"action": "start"}                                    ← legacy fallback
    {"action": "stop"}                                     ← legacy fallback
    {"action": "startWindowHeating"}                       ← legacy fallback
    {"action": "stopWindowHeating"}                        ← legacy fallback

  Temperature is in Kelvin (e.g. 22 °C = 295.15 K).

  Implementation:
  - cariad/api/seat_cupra.py:command_set_climate_temperature (line ~822) —
    primary path for setting climate target temperature.
  - command_start_climate / command_stop_climate — A/B fallback on 404
    from /v2/vehicles/{vin}/climatisation/{action} (seq 03 / 24).
  - command_start_window_heating / command_stop_window_heating — A/B
    fallback (seq 29 / 30).
}
